# Features — [App Name] Clone

> Output of Phase 1 (Research) in `pipeline/build/ORCHESTRATOR_BRIEF.md`.
> Replace this template with your findings. Copy to `spec/FEATURES.md` first.

## Document contract (read before editing)

This file is one of four that must stay in sync. If you change one, update
the others in the same commit.

- `pipeline/build/ORCHESTRATOR_BRIEF.md` — the pipeline. Owns: phases,
  exit conditions, gates, subagent split. Reads: this file, `RESEARCH.md`,
  `TASK_PLAN.md`.
- `spec/FEATURES.md` (this file) — the scope. Owns: feature inventory,
  Tier 1 vs Tier 2 split, failure-mode targets, seed data totals. Reads:
  `spec/RESEARCH.md` (tokens), `spec/TASK_PLAN.md` (task-driven seed).
- `spec/RESEARCH.md` — the UI spec. Owns: screenshots, design tokens,
  per-page layout, interactive state matrix, testids. Reads: this file.
- `spec/TASK_PLAN.md` — the task spec. Owns: failure-mode selection,
  per-task end-state, difficulty, seed-determinism mapping. Reads: this
  file (which entities exist) and `pipeline/qa/TASK-PROCESS.md`.

Agreement rules:
- Every page listed in `RESEARCH.md` § "Per-page layout spec" must appear
  here with a tier assignment. Every Tier 1 / Tier 2 feature here must
  have a layout subsection in `RESEARCH.md`.
- Every entity referenced in `TASK_PLAN.md` must exist in this file's
  feature inventory and in Phase 2's System Plan entity list.
- If you add, remove, or re-tier a feature, update all four files in the
  same commit.

